ct to the mailbox but enables you to sort your mailbox properly<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDM'),('Description of your mailbox<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDN'),('Address of the server you connect to.<br>Example : imap.gmail.com<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDO'),('Username used to connect to the mailbox.<br>Example : myname@gmail.com<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDP'),('Password used to connect to the mailbox<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDQ'),('Port used to connect to the server<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDR'),('Does the account requires a secure connection?<br>','1','1241989377TGDS'),('Select the system of connection you want to use<br>','1','1241989377TGDT'),('The system won\'t automatically handle the messages for a non published mailbox.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDU'),('If the received message has not been deleted by any plugin, should the system delete the message?<br>If you select \"No\", the e-mail will stay in the mailbox until you manually delete it.<br>This option should be turned OFF  and you should rather use the \"forward\" or the \"save message\" capability.<br>','1','1241989377TGDV'),('Should the system forward the message (store in Inbox) to another e-mail address?<br><br>If so, please specify the e-mail address in this field.<br>If you leave this field empty, the system won\'t forward the e-mail.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDW'),('The system can save the message so you can easily see it if necessary.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDX'),('Regex used to identify a bounce back e-mail.<br>This regex is executed on the subject and the sender of the received message.<br>Please do not modify this value if you don\'t know how works regex and bounce back messages!<br>','1','1241989377TGDY'),('Set the time (in seconds) the system will try to connect to your mailbox.<br>If you enter the value 0, the default time out of your php configuration will be applied.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGDZ'),('Subject of the received message<br><br>','1','1241989377TGEA'),('Content of the message<br>','1','1241989377TGEB'),('Header informations<br><br>','1','1241989377TGEC'),('Maximum number of messages the system will handle per mailbox.<br>If you set this preference to 0, the system will not handle any messages in each mailbox. Please provide a value other than 0 by default this is set to 50.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGED'),('Automatically delete the statistics if the latest received date is older than X days.<br>If you enter 0, the statistics will never be deleted automatically.<br>','1','1241989377TGEE'),('Automatically delete messages if the message has been handled more than X days in the past.<br>If you enter 0, the system won\'t delete automatically the messages.<br><br>','1','1241989377TGEF'),('Server','1','1241989377TGEG'),('Port','1','1241989377TGEH'),('Secure Method','1','1241989377TGEI'),('Connection Method','1','1241989377TGEJ'),('Forward','1','1241989377TGEK'),('Save the message','1','1241989377TGEL'),('Bounce Regex','1','1241989377TGEM'),('Open time out','1','1241989377TGEN'),('Maximum number of messages','1','1241989377TGEO'),('Auto Delete Stats','1','1241989377TGEP'),('Auto Delete Messages','1','1241989377TGEQ'),('body','1','1241989377TGER'),('Mailboxes','1','1241989377TGES'),('This screen enables you to create or modify a mail account so the system can connect to it and handle the messages.<br><br><ul><li>If you click on the button \"Connect\", the system will save your configuration and try to connect to your mailbox so that you can easily test the connection.<br></li></ul>','1','1241989377TGEV'),('This view shows you a list of messages which have been processed and stored into this box.<br><ul><li>You can click on the subject of the message to see the entire message in a popup.</li></ul>','1','1241989377TGEW'),('This view enables you to configure the global preferences used by the system and by all plugins.<br><br>You will find more detailed preferences for each plugin and for each mailbox.<br>','1','1241989377TGEX'),('The statistics have been deleted','1','1241989381TANT'),('E-mail Plugin','1','1241989381TANV'),('First date','1','1241989381TANW'),('Latest date','1','1241989381TANX'),('Purge','1','1241989381TANY'),('The following assigned widgets to the mailbox will be executed when the system handle the messages.<br>Even if a widget does delete the message (because the widget could handle it), the other widgets will be triggered.<br><ul><li>You can assign widget(s) to the mailbox by just clicking on the No link.</li><li>You can remove the assignment of widget(s) to the mailbox if you click on the Yes link.</li><li>Make sure you properly ordered the assigned widgets to the mailbox so that the messages will be handled properly.<br></li></ul>','1','1241989381TAOF'),('This view displays the statistics for the messages identified by the system (which are not the messages the system received but really the messages which have been recognized as a certain type and handled by the system).<br><br>For each identified e-mail address and for each type of message, you can see when the first message has been handled, the latest time a message has been received and how many messages the system handled.<br><br><ul><li>The button \"Purge\" enables you to delete all statistics from your database.</li></ul>','1','1241989381TAOH'),('Messages statistics','1','1241989381TAOJ'),('Do you want the system to delete the Acajoom Subscriber ?<br>If you select \"No\", the user will always stay in Acajoom.<br>If you select \"Yes\", the user will be deleted from Acajoom so he will be also unsubscribed from all your lists.<br>','1','1241989760RVBE'),('Do you want the system to unsubscribe the user from all Acajoom lists?<br>','1','1241989760RVBF'),('Specify if you want the system to unconfirm the subscriber.<br>Acajoom won\'t send e-mails to an unconfirmed subscriber.<br>','1','1241989760RVBG'),('Specify the minimum number of bounced back e-mails the system should receive before executing the following actions.<br>If you specify 0, the subscriber will never be deleted, unsubscribed or unconfirmed.<br>','1','1241989760RVBH'),('Once the system identified the message as a bounced back, should the system delete the message?<br>If you don\'t delete the message, the system may handle it twice so this option should be turn OFF only on debug mode.<br>','1','1241989760RVBI');
INSERT IGNORE INTO `#__translation_en` (`text`,`auto`,`imac`) VALUES ('You can subscribe the user to one Newsletter list<br><br>','1','1241989760RVBJ'),('Specify the minimum delay (in days) between the first received bounced back message and the latest received bounced back message.<br><br><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Example</span> : if you specify 3 (which means 3 days), the system will only execute the following actions if there are minimum X bounced back messages received and the elapsed time between the first received bounced back and the latest one is minimum 3 days.<br><br>','1','1241989760RVBK'),('Delete the subscriber','1','1241989760RVBL'),('Unsubscribe the user','1','1241989760RVBM'),('Unconfirm the subscriber','1','1241989760RVBN'),('Delete message','1','1241989760RVBP'),('Subscribe the user','1','1241989760RVBQ'),('Minimum Delay','1','1241989760RVBR'),('Conditions','1','1241989760RVBS'),('This plugin enables you to handle the bounced back messages for jNews so that your list of subscribers keeps only real subscribers.<br><br>Oncethe system will receive X bounced back messages for the same subscriberand the delay between the first received message and the latest one isminimum Y days, this subscriber can be automatically : <br><ul><li>Unsubscribed from all your lists</li><li>Subscribed to an other Newsletter list</li><li>Unconfirmed</li><li>Black listed<br></li><li>Deleted</li></ul>','1','1241989760RVBU'),('Done','1','1242282449PIPC'),('ERROR : Could not connect to the mailbox $MAILBOX_NAME','1','1242580111TAIP'),('Successfully connected to the mailbox $MAILBOX_NAME','1','1242580111TAIQ'),('Message $SUBJECT forwarded to $EMAIL_ADDRESS','1','1242580111TAIS'),('Could not forward the message $SUBJECT to $EMAIL_ADDRESS','1','1242580111TAIT'),('When a message is parsed to detect which e-mail address it comes from (this e-mail address is always in the content of the message), the system may identify an e-mail address which is not the right one.<br>To avoid this problem, you can specify in this field a list of e-mail address which should not be identified by the system.<br>Each e-mail address should be separated by the character |.<br><br><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Example</span> : If you don\'t want the system to identify any email address which comes from the domain mywebsite.com, you can simply write in this field @mywebsite.com<br><br>','1','1242580112DTJX'),('Email detector','1','1242580112DTJY'),('This view enables you to create, modify and test the connection to one or several mail accounts.<br><br>To configure the system properly, you have to:<br><ol><li>Click on the button \"New\" to configure the connection to your Mailbox.</li><li>Test the connection via the button \"Connect\".</li><li>If the Connection succeed, you can select your Mailbox and click on the button \"Process\" to handle the messages and trigger the assigned widgets.</li></ol><ul><li>If you select a mail account and click on the button \"Connect\", the system will try to connect to the mail account so that you can test the connection.<br></li><li>The button \"Process\" will enable to system to connect to the selected mailbox and handle the messages.</li><li>This process can be done automatically with a scheduler but only on published Mailboxes.<br></li><li>If you delete a Mailbox, the messages received for this mailbox will be also deleted.<br></li></ul>','1','1242580112DTJZ'),('If you select Yes, the user will be blacklisted.<br>Acajoom does not send any e-mail to a blacklisted user.<br><br>','1','1242580122OOGT'),('Number of Bounces','1','1242580122OOGU'),('Blacklist the subscriber','1','1242580122OOGV'),('If you select \"Yes\", the system won\'t require the validation of certificates from TLS/SSL server.<br>This option is needed if            your server uses self-signed certificates.<br><br>','1','1244722787NNCA'),('Self-signed Certificates','1','1244722788BFSH'),('Sent','1','1249453427FZXK'),('Enter words to be added into the dictionary for filtering purposes.<br>','1','1251697924MLJL'),('Specify where the words will be search in the message.<br>','1','1251697924MLJM'),('Select the type of message where these words belong.<br><br>Note:  <br>You can\'t select All Types because there\'s no available filter for All Types of Message. This is only use for default value purposes.<br>','1','1251697924MLJN'),('Entry','1','1251697924MLJO'),('Words','1','1251697924MLJP'),('SearchIn','1','1251697924MLJQ'),('Entry number','1','1251697924MLJR'),('Words to be search.','1','1251697924MLJS'),('Where to search the words either in the body, subject of the message or both.','1','1251697924MLJT'),('Type of the message','1','1251697924MLJU'),('To determine if the entry is predefined or not.','1','1251697924MLJV'),('The date the entry is added.','1','1251697924MLJW'),('If the Entry is publish or not.','1','1251697924MLJX'),('ID of the entry','1','1251697924MLJY'),('Create or add entry to the dictionary.<br>','1','1251697925DNIJ'),('Used for forwarding of messages to a certain email account.<br>','1','1251697925DNIK'),('Delete Forever','1','1251697925DNIL'),('Dictionary','1','1251697925DNIM'),('Dictionary Entry','1','1251697925DNIN'),('This view shows you a list of messages which have been received in your mailboxes.<br>You can configure each mailbox so that the system will keep the messages in the database or not.<br><br>The Sender displayed on this view is not always the real sender of the message and will be the identified e-mail address for bounced back e-mails so that you can easily search for messages which bounced from a certain e-mail address.<br><br><ul><li>You can click on the subject of the message to see the entire message in a popup.</li></ul>','1','1251697925DNIO'),('This view shows you a list of messages which have been sent.<br><ul><li>You can click on the subject of the message to see the entire message in a popup.</li></ul>','1','1251697925DNIQ'),('Controller for Bounceback Dictionary.<br>','1','1251697926LPNG'),('Controller for Trash Menu.<br>','1','1251697926LPNI'),('Controller for adding enty in the dictionary.<br><br>','1','1251697926LPNJ'),('mailbox-dictionary','1','1251697926LPNL'),('mailbox-trash','1','1251697926LPNN'),('mailbox-archive','1','1251697926LPNO'),('Mailbox Widgets','1','1251697930IGYM'),('Assigned Widgets','1','1251697930IGYN'),('Tips/Guidelines','1','1253693139FSTT'),('There is still $NUMBEROFMESSAGE to retrieved','1','1254227304QDMN'),('rule','1','1254227305KKYZ'),('rule.condition','1','1254227305KKZB'),('Search In','1','1254227306FJFO'),('Autoreply Message forwarded to $sender','1','1254392738GVKF'),('Could not forward the Autoreply to $sender','1','1254392738GVKG'),('There are no available messages to be filtered.','1','1254392738GVKH'),('Upon processing the mailbox, should the system delete the message or email from your external mailbox?<br><br>If you select \"No\", the e-mails will stay in the external mailbox until you manually delete it.<br><br>If you select \"Yes\" the emails will be automatically removed from your external mailbox.<br><br>This option should be turn \"ON\" inorder not to retrieve the same messages everytime and to retrieve the next batch of messages from your external mailbox specially when you have messages more than the preference you specify.<br>','1','1256863992BRRE'),('Delete Emails','1','1256863993QDJG'),('Trash Box Frequency','1','1256863993QDJH'),('Ordering of Entries','1','1256863993QDJI'),('If the entry is to be used for the filtering of the message we need to Publish the entry.<br>','1','1257414617RUXN'),('You need to put value in the Maximum number of messages from the Mailbox Preferences other than 0','1','1258010751GXJB'),('This scheduler extension is to automatically remove the messages stored in the Trash Box depending on the specified date.','1','1260253904QSSO'),('Empty Trash Box','1','1260253904QSSP'),('Automatically delete messages from Trash Box according to X days you specify here. <br><br>The frequency is based on Days.<br>If you enter 0, the system won\'t delete automatically the messages.<br>','1','1260253911PVFX'),('This view shows you a list of messages which have been filtered directly from inbox and stored into this box.<br><ul><li>You can click on the subject of the message to see the entire message in a popup.</li></ul>','1','1260253912CIOM'),('No. Of Bounced Messages','1','1263527488PFLQ'),('Mailbox Name','1','1263527488PFLR'),('No. Of Messages','1','1263527488PFLS'),('Bounce Messages Report','1','1263527489DDRU'),('Mailboxes Report','1','1263527489DDRV'),('jNews Bounce Preferences','1','1267609148IZGA'),('<br>This view shows you the entries of words which can be found in the subject, body and in both parts of the message for filtering process.<br><br>You can add entries for your own filters depending on what type of message they belong.<br><ul><li>The core column tells you that the entry can be exported.<br><br></li><li>If you want to delete the given entries you may have to uncore them first.<br><br></li></ul><br>','1','1275727304KGSY'),('<p>This report shows how many Bounced Messages. By default, <strong>the report is generated by interval of Weekly of This Month range.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To <strong>change the date range of the generated report</strong>, select the range in the drop down list then it will automatically generated the report.</li>\r\n	<li>To <strong>generate a report on a specific date</strong>, select the start and end date in the specified date group, then click generate button.</li>\r\n	<li>Report Type radio list is to change the view of report whether to display data in Graph or Data Listing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 51, 255)\">*NOTE:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Click Refresh Button</strong>, if you change the intervals to reload the page.</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>Reference Time is the Time Zone in the Local Settings of your Joomla Website Configuration.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>For the Line Graph, the big graph is the relative data values of all data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','1','1275727304KGSZ'),('<p>This report shows how many Messages bounced on each Mailbox. By default, <strong>the report is generated by interval of Weekly of This Month range.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To <strong>change the date range of the generated report</strong>, select the range in the drop down list then it will automatically generated the report.</li>\r\n	<li>To <strong>generate a report on a specific date</strong>, select the start and end date in the specified date group, then click generate button.</li>\r\n	<li>Report Type radio list is to change the view of report whether to display data in Graph or Data Listing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 51, 255)\">*NOTE:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Click Refresh Button</strong>, if you change the intervals to reload the page.</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>Reference Time is the Time Zone in the Local Settings of your Joomla Website Configuration.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','1','1275727304KGTA'),('This view enables you to see and configure any widget triggered by the system.<br><ul><li>You can affect each widget to one or several mailbox accounts so that when a message is handled, each assigned widget will be triggered.</li><li>Some of those widgets can be configured to meet your needs.</li><li>You can click on the little preferences icon to do so.<br></li><li>The system is able to connect to a mailbox and handle the messages so if you have other ideas for widgets, don\'t hesitate to submit them to the Joobi team, they will be happy to develop them!</li></ul><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 153); font-weight: bold;\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 153); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Hint</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">:</span> U